cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with the problem of extracting structured information from unstructured text, which is a common theme in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for constructing reference sets, which suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The reference sets are used for information extraction, which is a task in both cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases).
